This paper deals with entity-level sentiment analysis in Arabic, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of morphological representations and distributional semantic clusters to improve the performance of sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these fields are also relevant to the techniques used in the paper.
